event.title: was set off as Aishcum County in 1840

data.event: The county was set off as Aishcum County in 1840.
In 1843 it was renamed Lake, for its many lakes.
It was organized in 1871 As of the census of 2000, there were 11,333 people, 4,704 households, and 3,052 families residing in the county.
